<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920228-0086</DOCNO><DOCID>920228-0086.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Hoechst AG:   Unit Sues Allied-Signal Inc.,   Alleging Patent Infringement</HL><DATE>02/28/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C10</SO><CO>   ALD G.HFA</CO><MS>BASIC MATERIALS (BSC)INDUSTRIAL (IDU)</MS><IN>CHEMICALS, PLASTICS (CHM)DIVERSIFIED INDUSTRIAL (IDD)</IN><NS>PATENTS (PAT)</NS><RE>EUROPE (EU)GERMANY (GE)NEW JERSEY (NJ)NORTH AMERICA (NME)UNITED STATES (US)WESTERN EUROPE (WEU)</RE><LP>   Hoechst Celanese Corp. said it sued Allied-Signal Inc.,alleging infringement of two patents relating to thepolyester yarn used in radial tires.   Hoechst said the yarns, known as high modulus, lowshrinkage fibers, were introduced in 1980 and quicklyreplaced conventional yarns in the high-performance tires ofmany manufacturers. The suit by the Somerville, N.J., unit ofHoechst AG of Germany, was filed in federal district court inCharlotte, N.C.</LP><TEXT>   A spokesman for Allied-Signal said the Morristown, N.J.,company had been aware of Hoechst's concerns prior to thesuit's filing and had determined that neither itsmanufacturing process nor the product infringes on Hoechst'spatents. He said Allied-Signal intends to &quot;vigorously defend&quot;itself against the suit.</TEXT></DOC>